<title>ITALY: Bank of Italy buying back up to 1.5 trln lire BOTs.</title>
<headline>Bank of Italy buying back up to 1.5 trln lire BOTs.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-04-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Bank of Italy said it would buy back up to 1.5 trillion lire of short term bills (BOT) expiring between July 31, 1997 and November 28, 1997.</p>
<p>Bids must be received by 0815 GMT.</p>
